-- Manchester City Beats Chelsea 2-0 in England’s Premier League
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2013-02-24T15:39:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-24/manchester-city-beats-chelsea-2-0-in-england-s-premier-league.html
Defending champion Manchester City
beat Chelsea 2-0 in English soccer’s Premier League today and
still trails leader Manchester United by 12 points after the
weekend’s games. Newcastle defeated Southampton 4-2.  Yaya Toure and Carlos Tevez got the goals for City after
Frank Lampard, seeking his 200th goal for Chelsea, saw his
penalty kick saved by Joe Hart.  Yesterday United won 2-0 at bottom club Queens Park
Rangers. It has 68 points, followed by City (56), Chelsea (49)
and Tottenham (48).  QPR has 17 points, with Reading (23) and Aston Villa (24)
in the other two places in the relegation zone. Wigan also has
24 points and Southampton 27. Newcastle is in 14th spot with 30
points.  Yesterday, Arsenal beat Aston Villa 2-1 and Norwich
defeated Everton by the same score. Fulham had a 1-0 victory
over Stoke, Wigan won 3-0 at Reading, and Sunderland went down
2-1 at West Brom. West Ham hosts Tottenham tomorrow.  Later today, Swansea City meets Bradford City in the League
Cup final at Wembley.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Elser at   celser@bloomberg.net . 